KSM-Helper

This module provides a number of commonly used functions to expedite writing your program.

All library functions here use references to hashes and arrays instead
of hash or arrays directly.

Code examples in the documentation assiume the :all export tag is
imported by your code.  See the EXPORT section of 'perldoc
KSM::Helper' for an example of how to do this.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc KSM::Helper

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=KSM-Helper

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/KSM-Helper

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/KSM-Helper

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/KSM-Helper/


